snippet.textDisplay:
Boxing is so pathetic sometimes. People need to start fighting people who are worthy and stop padding their records against nobody's. One would say they need the experience to grow, that's why they fight lower calibre fighters. In all honesty, it makes them look pathetic and it hurts business. FANS want to see FIGHTERS, fight the BEST or SAME CALIBRE of FIGHTERS.


Ryan Garcia looked like a huge bitch during his post-fight speech. Devin Haney called him out, right to his face, and what did Ryan do? Ryan played it off as a joke, and calls out other fighters, that he damn well-knows he would never fight anytime soon.


It's disgraceful when Boxers bullshit on the microphone, or through any media to gain a few likes and followers. I get that Boxing is a business, but fighters need to stop lying to the fans, and stop this record padding bullshit!
